crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
The code is a batch script that attempts to elevate its privileges using the UAC. If successful, it will then install a file named d2ef5.exe in the %APPDATA% directory.

This file is likely to be malicious, as it is not a legitimate Windows file. It is possible that it could be used to install additional malware or ransomware.

It is recommended that you do not run this code. If you have already run it, you should scan your computer for malware and remove any suspicious files.
